{
  "id": 4841046007742464,
  "name": "CSS contrast-color()",
  "summary": "This function is used to meet contrast requirements for accessibility.\n\nThe contrast-color() function can be used anywhere in CSS where a color value is expected. It takes a color value argument, and returns either 'black' or 'white' depending on which of them gives the highest contrast against the color argument.\n",
